<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The internal representation is a &#42;strip&#42;, a sequence of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; operators ending with an endmarker.  (Some terminology etc. is a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="52"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; historical relic of earlier versions which used multiple strips.)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="53"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Certain oddities in the representation are there to permit running</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; the machinery backwards; in particular, any deviation from sequential</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="55"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; flow must be marked at both its source and its destination.  Some</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; fine points:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; - OPLUS&#95; and O&#95;PLUS are &#42;inside&#42; the loop they create.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; - OQUEST&#95; and O&#95;QUEST are &#42;outside&#42; the bypass they create.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; - OCH&#95; and O&#95;CH are &#42;outside&#42; the multi-way branch they create, while</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;   OOR1 and OOR2 are respectively the end and the beginning of one of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;   the branches.  Note that there is an implicit OOR2 following OCH&#95;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;   and an implicit OOR1 preceding O&#95;CH.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; In state representations, an operator&#39;s bit is on to signify a state</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Structure for &#91;&#93; character-set representation.  Character sets are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; done as bit vectors, grouped 8 to a byte vector for compactness.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The individual set therefore has both a pointer to the byte vector</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; and a mask to pick out the relevant bit of each byte.  A hash code</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="104"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; simplifies testing whether two sets could be identical.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="105"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="106"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; This will get trickier for multicharacter collating elements.  As</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="107"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; preliminary hooks for dealing with such things, we also carry along</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="108"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; a string of multi-character elements, and decide the size of the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="109"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; vectors at run time.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="110"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
